info.description:
# Introduction

This configuration file is designed to be a basis for all configurations provided by Opencell.
It merely contains most common general settings and a catalog of services implementing various rating models.

# Configuring Opencell

There are 2 main ways for configuring ***Opencell***:
* GUI (*Administration GUI* and *Marketing Manager*)
* API (all Opencell configuration and operations can be performed using our extensive API library)

The most flexible way is using APIs which currently are available as **Rest** and **Soap**.
The **Soap** API are deprecated, so will won't mention them anymore.

## Tools

Any tools able to send HTTP requests will do.
One could even just script *curl* calls using shell script.
But of course, a more user friendly tool will make things easier.

Here at ***Opencell***, we prefer **Postman** (https://getpostman.com):
* it has a modern, friendly interface
* Sets of API request can be organized into collections, themselves structured into a folder tree.
* Collections can be exported as _JSON_ files or shared with other team members using collaboration features (payed version)
* it allows to uses variables at different levels (collection, environement, global) and to execute *Javascript* scripts before and after executing API calls which allows great flexibility and API response testing.



# Configuration documentation guidelines

In order to document our configuration, we make full used of the internal documentation capabilities of the Markdown fields on Postman Objects

## Default template for *Collection* documentation

## Default template for *Folder* documentation

## Default template for *Request* documentation



# Tips & guidelines

Here follow a few tips for understanding this collection.

## Collection pre-request script

```javascript
pm.globals.set("timestamp.iso", (new Date()).toISOString());
pm.globals.set("request.label", pm.info.requestName);

var parts = pm.info.requestName.split("|");

for(let i=0; i<parts.length; i++) {
    pm.globals.set("request.label."+i, parts[i]);
}
```

## Configuration guidelines

## Entities

<entity>_<project_code>_XXX

### Custom Fields

CF_<entity>_<project_code>_ XXX

<entity> will be discarded for inherited

#### Custom field visibility

SE_<entity>_<project_code>_<markers>_XXX

<markers> are used in CFT.applicableOnEl to show CFT on entities


## Entity abbreviation

| code  | entity                        |
|:-----:|:------------------------------|
|   P   | Provider                      |
|   S   | Seller                        |
|   C   | Customer                      |
|  CA   | Customer Account              |
|  BA   | Billing Account               |
|  UA   | User Account                  |
|  SU   | Subscription                  |
|  AP   | Access Point                  |
|  OF   | Offer Template                |
|  SE   | Service Template and Instance |
|  CH   | Charge Template               |
|  PP   | Price Plan                    |
|  CN   | Counter                       |
| ICAT  | Invoice Category              |
| ISCAT | Invoice SubCategory           |
|  CAL  | Calendar                      |
|  BC   | Billing Cycle                 |

item.name: SCRIPT|CreateAccess|Creates an access on Subscription creation

body.raw:
<ScriptInstance code="org.meveo.service.script.{{request.label.1}}" description="{{request.label.2}} {{$timestamp}}">
        <type>JAVA</type>
        <script><![CDATA[
package org.meveo.service.script;

import java.util.Date;
import java.util.Map;

import org.meveo.admin.exception.BusinessException;
import org.meveo.model.admin.User;
import org.meveo.model.billing.Subscription;
import org.meveo.model.mediation.Access;

import org.meveo.service.medina.impl.AccessService;
import org.meveo.service.script.Script;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

public class CreateAccess extends Script {    
    private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(CreateAccess.class);        

    private AccessService accessService = (AccessService) getServiceInterface("AccessService");

    @Override
    public void execute(Map<String, Object> context) throws BusinessException {
        log.info("EXECUTE context={}", context);

        Subscription subscription = (Subscription) context.get("entity");
        if(subscription == null){
            throw new BusinessException("subscription is null");
        }
        log.debug("subscription={}", subscription);

        Access access = new Access();
        access.setSubscription(subscription);
        access.setAccessUserId(subscription.getCode());
        access.setStartDate(null);
        access.setEndDate(null);
        accessService.create(access);
    }
}]]></script>
</ScriptInstance>

<ScriptInstance code="org.meveo.service.script.{{request.label.1}}" description="{{request.label.2}} {{$timestamp}}">
        
        <type>JAVA</type>
        <script><![CDATA[
package org.meveo.service.script;

import java.math.BigDecimal;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;

import org.meveo.admin.exception.BusinessException;
import org.meveo.event.CounterPeriodEvent;
import org.meveo.model.billing.CounterPeriod;
import org.meveo.model.billing.ServiceInstance;
import org.meveo.model.billing.Subscription;
import org.meveo.model.billing.UserAccount;
import org.meveo.model.catalog.ServiceTemplate;
import org.meveo.service.billing.impl.CounterPeriodService;
import org.meveo.service.billing.impl.ServiceInstanceService;
import org.meveo.service.crm.impl.CustomFieldInstanceService;
import org.meveo.service.script.Script;

public class counterPeriodResetToInitialValue extends Script {



    @Override
    public void init(Map < String, Object > methodContext) throws BusinessException {
        log.info("EXECUTE-------------- counterPeriodResetToInitialValue script is processing...");

    }


    @Override
    public void execute(Map < String, Object > context) throws BusinessException {
        log.info("EXECUTE -------------- counterPeriodResetToInitialValue script is starting.......");

        CounterPeriod counterPeriod = null;
        CounterPeriod counterPeriodEvent = (CounterPeriod) context.get("entityOrEvent");
        if (counterPeriodEvent == null || counterPeriodEvent.getCounterInstance() == null) {
            throw new BusinessException("counterPeriod is null");
        }


        log.debug(">>>>>>>>>> counterPeriodEvent/code : " + counterPeriodEvent.getCode());
        log.debug(">>>>>>>>>> counterPeriodEvent/level : " + counterPeriodEvent.getLevel());
        log.debug(">>>>>>>>>> counterPeriodEvent/old value : " + counterPeriodEvent.getValue());

        counterPeriodEvent.setValue(counterPeriodEvent.getLevel());

        log.debug(">>>>>>>>>> counterPeriodEvent/ new value : " + counterPeriodEvent.getValue());

        log.info("EXECUTE -------------- counterPeriodResetToInitialValue script has successfully been executed");
    }




}

]]></script>
</ScriptInstance>
